Isolation Comments: isolated from an arsenic-rich alkaline soda lake in Nevada, Big Soda Lake
Additional Metadata: sample_type:Cell culture
Comments: Ectothiorhodospira sp. strain BSL-9 was isolated from an arsenic-rich alkaline soda lake in Nevada, Big Soda Lake. BSL-9 can grow photosynthetically by light-dependent oxidation of arsenite to arsenate, a less toxic form of arsenic. Genomic evidence suggest that BSL-9 uses an arx-type anaerobic arsenite oxidase and not the aio-type. 'Photoarsenotrophy' is thought to impact the arsenic biogeochemical cycle in shallow anoxic aquatic environments.

Isolation Source: hot spring microbial mat on Paoha Island
Isolation Comments: isolated from a hot spring microbial mat on Paoha Island in Mono Lake, CA
Comments: Ectothiorhodospira sp. PHS-1 was isolated from a hot spring microbial mat on Paoha Island in Mono Lake, CA.  These hot springs are enriched with high levels of arsenite.  Microbes such as PHS-1 can use this arsenite as an electron source for anaerobic photosynthesis.  This form of phototrophy may have predated the rise of atmospheric oxygen of the early earth.
This strain will be used for comparative analysis.
